Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses recent breakthroughs in Neural Architectural Search (NAS) and how it has achieved state-of-the-art performance in many tasks. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper mentions image classification as one of the tasks where NAS has achieved state-of-the-art performance. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the problem of NAS and how it can be extended to optimize for multiple objectives. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses the use of neural architectures in NAS and how they can be optimized for different objectives. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses the importance of considering hardware and devices when optimizing neural architectures for inference.
